title: Standish Cagney
text: Standish John Cagney (born 29 June 1900 - died 9 May 1962) was a <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player. He played thirteen <a href="Test%20match%20%28rugby%20union%29">tests</a> for the <a href="Ireland%20national%20rugby%20union%20team">Ireland national rugby union team</a>. His club team was <a href="London%20Irish">London Irish RFC</a>.
